'''Bumbita''' (But Arapesh) is an [[Arapesh language]] ([[Torricelli languages|Torricelli]]) of [[Papua New Guinea]] spoken mainly by older adults, unlike other Arapesh languages. Dialects are ''Bonahoi, Urita, Timingir, Weril, Werir.''
