'''Ghazan Marri''' ({{lang-ur|مير غزن مری}}) is a politician from [[Balochistan (Pakistan)|Balochistan]], [[Pakistan]].<ref name=a>{{cite news|url=http://article.wn.com/view/2006/09/02/Ghazan_Marri_being_tried_in_antiterrorist_court/|title=Ghazan Marri being tried in anti-terrorist court|publisher=World News|date=2 September 2006|accessdate=2010-12-12}}</ref> Marri is the son of politician [[Nawab Khair Bakhsh Marri]].<ref name=b>{{cite news|url=http://www.paktribune.com/news/index.shtml?141078|title=Ghazan Marri was wanted in a murder case: Sherpao|publisher=Pakistan Tribune|date=19 April 2006|accessdate=2010-12-12}}</ref> Marri's late brother, [[Balach Marri]], was also a politician.
In 2006, he was arrested in the [[United Arab Emirates]] at the request of the Pakistan authorities, in connection with the murder of judge Nawaz Marri.<ref name=b/> He was later tried in an anti-terrorist court in Pakistan.<ref name=a/>
In 2017, he returned to Pakistan, ending an 18-year exile in the UAE. Marri said he intended to face all court cases pending against him, and would join mainstream politics.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1513172/baloch-leader-ghazain-marri-arrested-lands-quetta-airport/|title=Right after arrival: Ghazain Marri arrested from Quetta airport|work=Express Tribune|date=22 September 2017|accessdate=23 September 2017}}</ref>
